README for ALPS developers

* How to make a snapshot?

1) Just type `make snapshot' at the top directory, which generates
   alps-YYYYMMDD.tar.gz and alps-light-YYYYMMDD.tar.gz, where YYYY =
   year, MM = month, and DD = day.


* How to update preamble of files?

1) Edit config/preamble.in.  Note that keywords @COPYRIGHT@ and @ID@
   will be replaced by appropriate strings.

2) Type make update-preamble at the top directory.


* [Checklist] How to release a new version and prepare the
  distribution file?

1) Check versions: Edit lines 14, 18, 31--33 in configure.ac.
   
2) Regenerate configure script by typing

     ./bootstrap

   at the top-level source directory.

3) Check all the documentations and ChangeLog.

4) ./configure && make update-preamble

5) make && make tests && make examples

6) svn commit

7) make snapshot

   Check alps-*.tar.gz and alps-light-*.tar.gz

   [[[Go to step 1, if you have a problem.]]]

8) make a tag for release

   ex) svn copy https://alps.comp-phys.org/svn/alps1/trunk/alps https://alps.comp-phys.org/svn/alps1/tags/alps-1.3

9) ./configure && make release

   alps-X.X.tar.gz
   alps-light-X.X.tar.gz

10) make boost-snapshot boost-sandbox-snapshot

    If the release is not based on an official Boost release make a Boost
    snapshot.

11) Copy the tar ball to the web server and update web page.
